Sec. 54.011. REPURCHASE OF STOCK. (a) A corporation formed
under this chapter may purchase, out of its available funds, any of
its outstanding stock.
(b) The corporation shall pay book value for stock purchased
under this section, as conclusively determined by the corporation's
directors.
(c) A corporation formed under this chapter shall state the
provisions of Subsections (a) and (b) of this section in its articles
of incorporation.
Acts 1981, 67th Leg., p. 1121, ch. 388, Sec. 1, eff. Sept. 1, 1981.

